{-
 - A very simple test game.
 - The player can move between two rooms.
 - There are no stats or items.
 -}

The player starts in room1 and is described by "You don't question your simple existence.".

A room is described by "You are in " + its name + ". There is a door here.".
Thing room1 is a room named "Room 1".
Thing room2 is a room named "Room 2".

Action "go through door" is available when location is room1, modifies player by
doing nothing, modifies current location by doing nothing before setting
location to room2, and is described by "You move to Room 2.".

Action "go through door" is available when location is room2, modifies player by
doing nothing, modifies current location by doing nothing before setting
location to room1, and is described by "You move to Room 1.".
